lenders.loan_because: Hunger in Brazil asking for help
lenders.occupational_info: The hunger in Brazil is sure to address: where there is poverty and lack of access to basic social rights. Even with the historic mobilization of civil society in the cause and implementation of public policies for food security, there are still all over the country who have no access to food in quantity and quality sufficient to maintain health. Child malnutrition gives the clearest signs of the problem in rural and urban areas. In Rio de Janeiro, the City of God, a survey conducted in 2008 showed that 22% of more than 2 thousand children surveyed were malnourished. (1) In Alagoas, 9.5% of children under 5 years have chronic malnutrition (low height for age) (2). ActionAid bet that the solution to hunger in the country is in stimulating sustainable food production at the local level, increasing the food supply in the region. We also need to enforce the legal mechanisms (laws and public policies) that already exist to ensure that nobody feels hungry.
